text.tspan: - zip the zipper close, removing the zipper pull
- re-insert the zipper pull from the end with no stop
- sew the zipper stop to the other end of the zipper
- sew the superior panel to the zipper with two seams
- first seam with the fabric edge and the zipper seam allowance edge matching
- second seam with the fabric folded over such that the fold line touches the zipper coils
- Sew the inferior panel to the zipper using the same method
- YKK #8 zipper is 3 cm wide: with 8 mm coil
- Seam allowance on panel is 1.1cm x 2 - 1.5cm
